- APIs at UI end and at BFF end have to be put in services.
- BFF can be on node js with express.js or nest.js
- The session management and caching other data has to be maintained centailly using redis or document store
- Each of the apis have to be protected by roles. The role definition document can be stored for each role 
in document store. The role definition document can contain CRUD role for each api/components and can be 
put in a the session  on login.



Security related:
-----------------
- Only the session id encrypted needs to be sent to UI. This will be automatically handled usign express sessions


